      <scopecontent id="aspace_99c33a521dbb7aa967b61a4715de2a2e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Yerkes papers document the work of the Presbyterian Church in the Shantung Province of China from 1869-1874 when Helen Yerkes' parents were stationed in Chefoo and from 1904-1950. Although they left China in 1925, Yerkes stayed in contact with his missionary and Chinese friends. Yerkes was involved with evangelical work as well as the administrative tasks of running the station. Among his duties, he served on the China Council and acted as treasurer of the station. From 1923 until his departure from China, he worked with the American Consulate, R.P. Tenney, to secure the release of foreign captives after the wreck of the "Blue Express" on May 6, 1923 and continued to supply information about the bandit situation in his area.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
